UML:TaggedValue.value:
context SdlCreateRequestNode
inv: ouput->notEmpty() implies output->get(0).type = classifier

context SdlCallNode
inv: procedure->size() + operationSignature->size() = 1 inv: argument->collect(type) = operation.parameter->collect(type) inv: target.type = operation.owner

context SdlAssignment
inv: structuralFeature.type = value.type inv: object.type = structuralFeature.owner

context SdlProcedure
inv: connectionPoint->isEmpty() inv: redefinedOperation->forAll(s|s.name = self.name) inv: name = region.name inv: specification = self and method = self

context SdlStartingTransition
inv: guard->isEmtpy() inv: kind = #local or kind = #external inv: source.oclIsKindOf(SdlState)
context SdlInputNode
inv: trigger.event.oclIsKindOf(UML::CommonBehavior::Communications::SignalEvent) inv. signal = trigger.event.oclAsType(UML::CommonBehavior::Communications::SignalEvent).signal
context SdlSpontaneiousTransition
inv: trigger.event.oclIsKindOf(UML::CommonBehavior::Communications::SignalEvent) inv. trigger.event.oclAsType(UML::CommonBehavior::Communications::SignalEvent).signal.name = "none"
context SdlContiniousSignal
inv: inv: trigger.event.oclIsKindOf(UML::CommonBehavior::Communications::ChangeEvent)

context SdlCompositeStateType
inv: isReentrant = false inv: general->forAll(g|g.name = self.name) inv: returnResult->isEmpty() inv: stateGraph->notEmpty implies region->contains(stateGraph) inv: stateAggregation->notEmpty implies stateAggregation->collect(partition.state)->forAll(p|self.region->containsAll(p.region) inv: region->forAll(r|r.name = self.name) inv: let signal:SDL::Structure::SdlSignal = region->collect(transition->collect(trigger.signal)) in signal->forAll(s1| not signal->exists(s2| s1 = s2))

context SdlStartNode inv: kind = #inital or kind = #entryPoint
context DecisionNode inv: kind = #choice
context SdlEntryPoint inv: kind = #entryPoint
context SdlNamedStartNode inv: kind = #inital or kind = #entryPoint or kind = #deepHistory inv: name = point.name
context SdlNamedReturnNode inv: kind = #exitPoint inv: name = point.name
context SdlExitPoint inv: kind = #exitPoint
context SdlStopNode inv: kind = #terminate
context SdlJoinNode inv: kind = #junction
context SdlFreeAction inv: kind = #junction

context SdlGate
inv: redefinedPort->forAll(name = self.name) inv: name->notEmpty() inv: aggregation = #composite inv: lowerValue = 1 inv: upperValue = 1 inv: isStatic = false inv: defaultValue->isEmtpy() inv: subsettedProperty->isEmpty()
context SdlChannelEnd
inv: partWithPort->isEmpty()

context SdlAgentType
inv: isConcurrent implies kind = #BLOCK inv: not isConcurrent implies kind = #PROCESS inv: name->notEmpty() inv: isActive = true inv: visibility = #public or visibility = #private inv: name = superAgent.name inv: not isConcurrent implies agentTypes->forAll(not isConcurrent) inv: classifierBehavior->notEmpty() implies classifierBehavior.specification = false

context SdlOperationSignature
inv: owner.oclTypeOf(SdlDataType) implies redefinedOperation->isEmtpy() inv: ownedParameter->forAll(p| p.type.oclTypeOf(SdlDataType))
context SdlProcedure
inv: ownedParameter->forAll(p| p.type.oclTypeOf(SdlDataType))

context SdlChannel
inv: type->isEmtpy() inv: isStatic = false inv: name->notEmpty() inv: let roles:Set(SdlGate) = end->collect(role) in roles->containsAll(path->collect(source)) and roles->containsAll(path->collect(target)) inv: path->size() < 3
context SdlChannelPath
inv: realization = owner
context SdlSignalList
inv: represented = signal
context SdlInterface
inv: represented = reception->collect(represented)

context SdlPackage
inv: packageExtension->isEmpty() inv: name->notEmpty() inv: visibility = #public or visibility = #private

context SdlInterface
inv: nestedInterface->isEmpty() inv: name->notEmtpy()

context SdlVariable
inv: name->notEmpty() inv: upper->size() = 1 inv: lower->size() = 1 inv: aggregation = #composite inv: subsettedProperty->size = 0
context SdlAgent
inv: name->notEmpty() inv: aggregation = #composite inv: subsettedProperty->size = 0

context SdlDataType
inv: name->notEmpty() inv: classifierBehavior->isEmpty() inv: ownedBehaviour #TODO# inv: ownedAttribute->isEmpty() #TODO-liteals, attribute# inv: name = superObjectDataType.name
context SdlObjectDataType
inv: isActive = false
context SdlPrimitiveType
inv: superValueDataType->isEmpty()
context SdlEnumeration
inv: superValueDataType->isEmpty()
OwnedAttributes and ownedOperation correspond to remote variables and operations or better the signatures of such.

There is a little discrepancy with UML. In UML I could model a property, for instance an agent, to have none aggregation semantics. I can do that in SDL, but I could map it to an SdlVariable of PID type (this is suggested by Z.109), but the meta-model does not state something like that. On the hand there is no sence in giving a SdlVariable none aggregation semantics, because it can only contain values with value semantics.
The multiplicity for variables is set to 1..1, but it could be meaningful to allow other multiplicities to model collection (types).
